So, if we're getting everything from a CDN, how do we run typescript type checks?

We need to download the dependencies so typescript can use them.
Then, we can generate import maps that match our local versions!

Unfortunately, I couldn't find an existing product that does this.
JSPM gets pretty close, but it doesn't have a story for typechecking.
So I vibe coded one. Enjoy!

--

Try `npm run dev` and check your web inspector to see the generated import map,
or use `npm run build` and check `dist/index.html`.
You'll see that all the transitive dependency versions are pinned in it.

You can also check the sources tab in your web inspector to see that our source code is small,
and all dependencies are coming from a CDN.

You can run `npm run typecheck` to type check it, and view the source code to see that intellisence works.
